The paper is about search personalization, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed approach involves learning user profiles through embeddings, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach using query logs, which is a common practice in studies related to search engines and information retrieval (cs.SI).
